2026-2027 from the Budget Reserve Trust Fund Account established in KRS 48.705 to the Department for Local
Government budget unit to be distributed to the Graves County Fiscal Court to support river cleanup.
Section 298. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of $928,000 in fiscal year
2026-2027 and $772,000 in fiscal year 2027-2028 from the Budget Reserve Trust Fund Account established in KRS
48.705 to the Department for Local Government budget unit to be distributed to the City of Auburn to support site
development at the Auburn Business Park and other city-owned properties.
Section 299. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of $1,000,000 in fiscal year
2026-2027 and $1,100,000 in fiscal year 2027-2028 from the Budget Reserve Trust Fund Account established in
KRS 48.705 to the Facilities and Support Services budget unit in the Finance and Administration Cabinet to replace
the Buckhorn Lake State Park Marina. The Finance and Administration Cabinet shall prioritize this project to address
public safety at Buckhorn Lake State Park.
Section 300. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of $250,000 in fiscal year
2026-2027 from the Budget Reserve Trust Fund Account established in KRS 48.705 to the Economic Development
budget unit to support a rural workforce study conducted in collaboration with the Kentucky Community and
Technical College System, the Education and Labor Cabinet, and other strategic partners to identify and develop
strategies addressing Kentucky’s long-term rural workforce needs.
Section 301. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of $250,000 in fiscal year
2026-2027 and $150,000 in fiscal year 2027-2028 from the Budget Reserve Trust Fund Account established in KRS
48.705 to the Department for Local Government budget unit to be distributed to the Laurel County Fiscal Court to
construct a new fire station.
Section 302. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of $250,000 in fiscal year
2026-2027 from the Budget Reserve Trust Fund Account established in KRS 48.705 to the Department for Local
Government budget unit to be distributed to the KY First Robotics, Inc. to support school programming.
Section 303. 2024 Ky. Acts ch. 173, sec. 1, subsec. (52) is amended to read as follows:
(52) $2,000,000 in fiscal year 2024-2025 to the Department for Local Government budget unit to be
distributed to the City of Paducah to support the Build Ready Grant for the City of Paducah Infrastructure project.
Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, these funds shall not lapse and shall carry forward;
Section 304. 2024 Ky. Acts ch. 173, sec. 1, subsec. (179), at page 1765, as amended by 2025 Ky. Acts ch.
162, sec. 5, at page 1121, is further amended to read as follows:
(179) $10,000,000 in fiscal year 2024-2025 to the Economic Development budget unit to be allocated to
Grayson County Fiscal Court for relocation of its county airport and to purchase acreage for a new industrial
development[the expansion of runways] to promote economic growth. Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, these funds
shall not lapse and shall carry forward;
Section 305. 2024 Ky. Acts ch. 173, sec. 1, subsec. (192), at page 1766, as amended by 2025 Ky. Acts ch.
117, sec. 37, subsec. 192, at page 717, is amended to read as follows:
(192) $6,000,000 in each fiscal year to the Community Based Services budget unit to be distributed to the
Life Learning Center to support an integrated pathway to treatment, rehabilitation, and community reintegration in

CHAPTER 142 25
partnership with a nonprofit located in Community Mental Health Region 13 or Region 14 to help administer
recovery and job placement services;
Section 306. Whereas the provisions of this Act provide ongoing support for state government agencies
and their functions, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by the
Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
Signed by Governor April 13, 2026.
